00:52:02.559 --> 00:52:03.979
the temptations that I'll face,

00:52:03.979 --> 00:52:06.879
I'll be blessed by God, I'll be rewarded by God,

00:52:06.879 --> 00:52:09.399
and I want God's blessing.

00:52:09.399 --> 00:52:11.079
I want God's reward.

00:52:11.079 --> 00:52:13.759
It doesn't matter, listen, it should not matter to you

00:52:13.759 --> 00:52:16.479
what accolades some man can give you.

00:52:16.479 --> 00:52:17.999
It should matter, and I understand,

00:52:17.999 --> 00:52:20.399
and I'm not saying that you shouldn't be concerned

00:52:20.399 --> 00:52:22.799
with regard to doing a good job and being the best

00:52:22.799 --> 00:52:24.419
that you can be and all of that sort of thing.

00:52:24.419 --> 00:52:26.759
I think that's commendable and it's appropriate.

00:52:26.759 --> 00:52:27.599
Why?

00:52:27.599 --> 00:52:29.079
Because whatsoever thy hand findeth to do,

00:52:29.079 --> 00:52:31.339
do it heartily as unto the Lord.

00:52:31.339 --> 00:52:33.279
And if you follow that principle,

00:52:33.279 --> 00:52:36.999
you will be recognized temporally.

00:52:36.999 --> 00:52:38.359
But that's not the focus.

00:52:39.339 --> 00:52:42.559
The focus is to have God's blessing,

00:52:44.499 --> 00:52:47.259
to have God's favor upon our lives.

00:52:48.379 --> 00:52:51.519
We ask the question, what kind of reward do you desire?

00:52:53.919 --> 00:52:55.339
I desire God's favor.

00:52:56.799 --> 00:53:00.599
Don't quit, don't quit.

00:53:00.599 --> 00:53:02.319
Somebody asked me this years ago.

00:53:03.839 --> 00:53:06.359
It was a Bible college professor.

00:53:06.359 --> 00:53:08.079
I believe it was William Jeffcoat,

00:53:08.079 --> 00:53:10.479
a man that we support as a missionary right now.

00:53:11.399 --> 00:53:13.959
And he asked a group of us in the class that day,

00:53:15.259 --> 00:53:17.599
what will it take to stop you?

00:53:20.919 --> 00:53:23.739
What will it take to stop you?

00:53:24.739 --> 00:53:28.019
In other words, what will it take to make you quit,

00:53:28.019 --> 00:53:31.259
to stop serving God, to give up?

00:53:33.219 --> 00:53:36.219
Can I tell you this morning, the answer should be nothing.

00:53:37.339 --> 00:53:38.919
I could tell you story after story.

00:53:38.919 --> 00:53:40.699
You could read them yourselves as well.

00:53:40.699 --> 00:53:42.139
You read the Fox's Book of Martyrs.

00:53:42.139 --> 00:53:46.559
You read of other martyrs, people that faced such cruelty.

00:53:47.899 --> 00:53:50.919
As they were literally being burned alive,

00:53:50.919 --> 00:53:52.619
they were singing praise unto God.

00:53:53.819 --> 00:53:58.299
They're testimonies of how God used them in that moment

00:53:58.299 --> 00:54:02.259
as they endured that great fiery trial.

00:54:02.259 --> 00:54:06.179
This morning, enduring trials, we all face them.

00:54:07.259 --> 00:54:09.659
We all face them, we all deal with them.

00:54:09.659 --> 00:54:13.619
The question is whether we endure through the trial.

00:54:13.619 --> 00:54:15.539
It's not gonna be by your strength or by my strength,

00:54:15.539 --> 00:54:18.939
it's by Him working through us and enabling us

00:54:18.939 --> 00:54:21.739
as we have that perspective and that approach

00:54:21.779 --> 00:54:25.139
that we understand that God has a purpose

00:54:25.139 --> 00:54:28.539
and I love Him because He first loved me.

00:54:29.779 --> 00:54:32.379
I don't know what you're dealing with.

00:54:32.379 --> 00:54:34.939
And quite honestly, not that I don't wanna be able

00:54:34.939 --> 00:54:37.779
to pray for you, but the reality is that I don't need

00:54:37.779 --> 00:54:41.479
to know because God knows.

00:54:43.099 --> 00:54:45.500
Whatever it is that you're facing,

00:54:45.500 --> 00:54:47.059
can I tell you this morning,

00:54:47.059 --> 00:54:49.459
can I encourage you this morning, endure.

00:54:50.299 --> 00:54:54.979
Don't give up, stay in the fight.

00:54:54.979 --> 00:54:57.579
The enemy wants you to be a casualty.

00:54:57.579 --> 00:54:59.219
He wants to devour you.

00:55:00.299 --> 00:55:03.899
But our God has a good plan and a good purpose for us

00:55:03.899 --> 00:55:07.659
and He's not trying to destroy us, but to develop us.

00:55:07.659 --> 00:55:08.479
Let us pray.

00:55:08.479 --> 00:55:09.659
Father, we love you.

00:55:09.659 --> 00:55:11.059
Thank you so much for loving us.

00:55:11.059 --> 00:55:14.619
Thank you, God, for the truth that you give us in your word.

00:55:15.619 --> 00:55:17.419
If we didn't have the Bible,

00:55:19.579 --> 00:55:24.339
we would not know the things that we discussed this morning.

00:55:25.619 --> 00:55:29.819
In fact, we might be like the friends of Job

00:55:29.819 --> 00:55:34.059
that we read of, that didn't have a complete understanding

00:55:34.059 --> 00:55:36.579
of what we now have having a whole Bible.

00:55:37.939 --> 00:55:40.299
God, I pray that you would help each one

00:55:40.299 --> 00:55:41.259
that's here this morning.

00:55:41.259 --> 00:55:43.619
Lord, I know that we face trials.

00:55:43.619 --> 00:55:46.779
In fact, I'm aware of some that are going

00:55:46.779 --> 00:55:47.899
through some trials.

00:55:49.059 --> 00:55:50.819
And Lord, I pray that you'd give us the grace

00:55:50.819 --> 00:55:53.099
and the strength and the help that we need.

00:55:53.099 --> 00:55:56.219
Help us to have our minds focused upon you and your word,

00:55:56.219 --> 00:56:00.739
our hearts completely surrendered to thee.

00:56:00.739 --> 00:56:04.500
Lord, help us to love you in response to your love for us.

00:56:04.500 --> 00:56:07.539
Help us to trust you, to follow you.

00:56:07.539 --> 00:56:09.259
Help us to abide in thee.

00:56:09.419 --> 00:56:12.179
Lord, I pray that you would help us now

00:56:13.019 --> 00:56:15.259
as we respond to what we've heard,

00:56:16.619 --> 00:56:18.899
to how your spirit has moved and worked,

00:56:18.899 --> 00:56:23.899
that Lord, you would help us to apply truth in our lives.

00:56:25.419 --> 00:56:26.899
Well, thank you for the work that you'll do

00:56:26.899 --> 00:56:28.219
for us in Christ's name, we pray.

00:56:28.219 --> 00:56:29.659
Would you stand with me?

00:56:29.659 --> 00:56:31.019
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed.

00:56:31.019 --> 00:56:33.059
We'll take a moment for an invitation.

00:56:33.059 --> 00:56:34.859
Maybe this morning you're just in the midst of a trial.

00:56:34.859 --> 00:56:37.659
You just need to have some time alone with God.

00:56:38.219 --> 00:56:39.500
Some time alone with God.

00:56:39.500 --> 00:56:41.379
Help me, Lord, I need your help.

00:56:42.859 --> 00:56:44.379
Maybe you know somebody that's going through a trial

00:56:44.379 --> 00:56:45.219
and you need to pray for them.

00:56:45.219 --> 00:56:46.259
Maybe you just want to come and ask God,

00:56:46.259 --> 00:56:47.299
I'm not in a trial right now,

00:56:47.299 --> 00:56:48.419
but I know trials are gonna come.

00:56:48.419 --> 00:56:50.139
Help me to endure.

00:56:50.139 --> 00:56:51.979
Help me to have the spiritual maturity.

00:56:51.979 --> 00:56:54.419
Help me to have the perspective that I need

00:56:54.419 --> 00:56:56.819
to endure the trials of life.

00:56:56.819 --> 00:56:58.699
I do not want to become a casualty.

00:56:58.699 --> 00:57:02.500
I do not want to quit in the face of opposition.

00:57:02.500 --> 00:57:04.539
As Kimberly plays, the altar is open.

00:57:04.539 --> 00:57:06.099
Christ is born.

